# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python version is
#   controlled by the user. See Aggregated Python Version Management for more details.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having no cross-platform support, pipenv may install dependencies that don't work, or even
#   fail to install all dependencies. In that case, Pipfile.lock should be ignored.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   However, for the same reasons as pipenv, it may be ignored in some cases.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
#pdm.lock
#   pdm stores project-wide configurations in .pdm-python
.pdm-python
#   pdm stores python packages in __pypackages__
__pypackages__/

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/lincc-frameworks/pdm2-pep582
__pypackages__/

